 COMPUTER SCIENCE AND ENGINEERING
Domain: Artificial and Machine learning

TITLE:  AI BASED TEXT SUMMARISATION TOOL
          ABSTRACT:
                AI Based Text Summarization Tool is designed to automatically generate concise summaries from large textual documents. The main objective of this system is to reduce the time required to read long articles, paragraphs, or documents by extracting the most important information. The system allows users to enter large text content through a simple and user-friendly web interface. It uses Natural Language Processing (NLP) techniques to analyze and understand the structure of the text. The tool identifies important sentences based on word frequency and relevance within the document. The system consists of several modules including Text Input, Text Preprocessing, Sentence Scoring, and Summary Generation. In the preprocessing stage, the system removes stop words, special symbols, and performs tokenization to prepare the text for analysis. The sentence scoring module evaluates and ranks sentences according to their importance. The highest-ranked sentences are then selected and combined to produce a meaningful and concise summary.The backend of the system is developed using Python with NLP libraries, while Flask is used to create the web application framework. The frontend interface is designed using HTML and CSS to provide a simple and user-friendly experience.This tool is highly useful for students, researchers, and professionals, as it helps them quickly understand large documents without reading the entire content.

Key Words: Artificial Intelligence, Text Summarization, Natural Language Processing, Python, Flask, Text Preprocessing, Tokenization, Sentence Ranking, Automatic Summary Generation, Web Application

