---

You are building a **Text Summarization Tool using a GitHub repository**, and you want the **Antigravity AI IDE agent** to upgrade it into a **modern, professional, and unique project**.

The main advantage of **Antigravity AI IDE** is that a **single prompt can allow the AI agent to perform planning, coding, testing, and UI design automatically**.

Therefore, you need to give a **very detailed prompt** to the agent.

---

# Exact Prompt for the Antigravity Agent

Copy and paste this prompt into the Antigravity agent:

```
Act as a senior AI engineer and full-stack architect.

Analyze my GitHub repository and upgrade the project into a modern, professional AI web application.

Project Goal:
Build a modern AI-powered Text Summarization Tool with a clean UI, scalable architecture, and production-ready design.

Repository:
https://github.com/shaiknurullaT2/MINOR-PROJECT.git

Requirements:

1. Backend
- Use Python with FastAPI instead of basic Flask
- Implement NLP-based text summarization
- Use modern NLP libraries such as spaCy or HuggingFace Transformers
- Add REST API endpoints for summarization
- Implement proper folder structure (controllers, services, models)
- Add input validation and error handling

2. AI Model
- Implement extractive and abstractive summarization
- Allow user to choose summary length (short / medium / long)
- Highlight key sentences
- Support large text input (articles, research papers)

3. Frontend
- Use React + Tailwind CSS
- Create a modern responsive UI
- Dark mode support
- Animated components
- Beautiful hero section
- Text input area with live character counter
- Summary output card with copy button

4. Unique Features
- PDF upload and summarization
- Word document summarization
- Article summarization from URL
- Summary download button
- Summary history dashboard

5. UI/UX
Design a professional SaaS-style interface similar to modern AI tools.

Pages:
- Landing page
- Summarization dashboard
- History page
- About project page

Use:
- Smooth animations
- Modern typography
- Glassmorphism or minimal design

6. Project Structure

Use a professional structure:

frontend/
backend/
api/
models/
services/
components/
pages/

7. Deployment

Prepare a deployment-ready setup:
- Docker support
- Deploy backend on Render
- Deploy frontend on Vercel
- Provide environment variables

8. Documentation

Generate:
- README.md
- API documentation
- Installation guide
- Deployment guide

9. Code Quality

Follow:
- Clean architecture
- PEP8 for Python
- Reusable components
- Proper comments

10. Final Output

Produce:
- Complete upgraded project
- Improved UI design
- Optimized AI summarization logic
- Ready-to-deploy full stack application
```

