I have fully implemented the persistent Auto-Login feature and verified that the React application compiles successfully.

What was done:

Global Auth Context (AuthContext.jsx): Replaced the basic string check with a robust React Context that explicitly tracks the user's isAuthenticated session securely.
Axios Interceptor (api.js): Built an intelligent API client. It automatically scoops up your token and attaches it to every single request backend request. More importantly, if your session ever expires (resulting in a 401 error), the interceptor catches it, elegantly clears your local token, and redirects you back to the login screen!
Smart Routing: Added a GuestRoute so that if you revisit the app and are already logged in, navigating anywhere near /login or /register instantly redirects you to your Dashboard!
Logout Feature: The pre-existing logout button in the Navbar was re-wired to properly use the global context logout() function, assuring a totally clean exit.
You can review the exact steps taken in the attached walkthrough. Let me know if you need any adjustments or if you are ready to implement some of those other amazing AI features you listed (like the Mind Map generator or Quiz Creator)
